  "response_text": "**Balanced Diet Plan for Weight Loss**\n\nA well-structured diet plan is essential for successful weight loss. This plan focuses on whole, nutrient-dense foods, portion control, and a balanced macronutrient ratio. The goal is to create a sustainable eating habit that promotes weight loss while maintaining overall health.\n\n**Daily Caloric Intake:**\nTo lose weight, you need to consume fewer calories than you burn. A safe and sustainable rate of weight loss is 1-2 pounds per week. Based on this, the daily caloric intake for weight loss is:\n\n* For women: 1500-1800 calories\n* For men: 2000-2500 calories\n\n**Macronutrient Ratio:**\nAim for a balanced macronutrient ratio of:\n\n* **Protein:** 15-20% of daily calories (0.8-1 gram per pound of body weight)\n* **Fat:** 20-30% of daily calories (0.5-1 gram per pound of body weight)\n* **Carbohydrates:** 55-65% of daily calories (2-3 grams per pound of body weight)\n\n**Food Groups:**\n\n1. **Vegetables:** 5-7 servings (aim for a variety of colors)\n\t* Dark leafy greens (broccoli, spinach, kale)\n\t* Cruciferous vegetables (cauliflower, bell peppers, carrots)\n\t* Root vegetables (sweet potatoes, beets, onions)\n2. **Fruits:** 2-3 servings\n\t* Berries (blueberries, strawberries, raspberries)\n\t* Citrus fruits (oranges, grapefruits, lemons)\n\t* Apples, bananas, and other whole fruits\n3. **Protein Sources:** 2-3 servings\n\t* Lean meats (chicken, turkey, fish)\n\t* Legumes (lentils, chickpeas, black beans)\n\t* Nuts and seeds (almonds, chia seeds, hemp seeds)\n4. **Whole Grains:** 2-3 servings\n\t* Brown rice, quinoa, whole wheat bread\n\t* Whole grain pasta, oats, and cereals\n5. **Dairy or Alternatives:** 2-3 servings\n\t* Low-fat milk, yogurt, and cheese\n\t* Plant-based milk alternatives (almond, soy, oat milk)\n\n**Meal Plan:**\n\n* **Breakfast:** Overnight oats with fruit and nuts (300 calories)\n* **Mid-Morning Snack:** Carrot sticks with hummus (100 calories)\n* **Lunch:** Grilled chicken breast with quinoa and roasted vegetables (400 calories)\n* **Mid-Afternoon Snack:** Apple slices with almond butter (150 calories)\n* **Dinner:** Baked salmon with sweet potato and green beans (500 calories)\n* **Before Bed Snack:** Greek yogurt with berries (150 calories)\n\n**Tips and Reminders:**\n\n1. **Stay hydrated:** Drink at least 8 cups (64 ounces) of water per day.\n2. **Watch portion sizes:** Eat until you're satisfied, not stuffed.\n3. **Incorporate physical activity:** Aim for at least 150 minutes of moderate-intensity exercise or 75 minutes of vigorous-intensity exercise per week.\n4. **Get enough sleep:** Aim for 7-9 hours of sleep per night to support weight loss and overall health.\n5. **Be mindful of your eating habits:** Eat slowly, savor your food, and avoid distractions while eating.\n\n**Sample Meal Plan:**\n\nHere's a sample 7-day meal plan:\n\nMonday:\n\n* Breakfast: Oatmeal with banana and almond butter (300 calories)\n* Lunch: Grilled chicken breast with brown rice and steamed broccoli (400 calories)\n* Dinner: Baked salmon with quinoa and roasted vegetables (500 calories)\n\nTuesday:\n\n* Breakfast: Scrambled eggs with whole wheat toast and avocado (250 calories)\n* Lunch: Turkey and avocado wrap with mixed greens (400 calories)\n* Dinner: Grilled chicken breast with roasted sweet potatoes and green beans (500 calories)\n\nWednesday:\n\n* Breakfast: Greek yogurt with berries and granola (200 calories)\n* Lunch: Lentil soup with whole grain bread (400 calories)\n* Dinner: Grilled shrimp with quinoa and steamed asparagus (400 calories)\n\nThursday:\n\n* Breakfast: Smoothie bowl with banana, spinach, and almond milk (300 calories)\n* Lunch: Grilled chicken breast with mixed greens and whole wheat pita (400 calories)\n* Dinner: Baked chicken thighs with roasted carrots and brown rice (500 calories)\n\nFriday:\n\n* Breakfast: Avocado toast with scrambled eggs and cherry tomatoes (250 calories)\n* Lunch: Turkey and cheese sandwich on whole wheat bread with a side salad (400 calories)\n* Dinner: Grilled salmon with quinoa and steamed green beans (500 calories)\n\nSaturday:\n\n* Breakfast: Omelette with vegetables and whole wheat toast (200 calories)\n* Lunch: Grilled chicken Caesar salad (400 calories)\n* Dinner: Baked chicken breast with roasted Brussels sprouts and sweet potatoes (500 calories)\n\nSunday:\n\n* Breakfast: Breakfast burrito with scrambled eggs, black beans, and avocado (300 calories)\n* Lunch: Grilled chicken breast with mixed greens and whole wheat wrap (400 calories)\n* Dinner: Baked salmon with quinoa and steamed asparagus (500 calories)\n\nRemember, this is just a sample meal plan, and you should adjust the portion sizes and food choices based on your individual needs and preferences. Consult with a healthcare professional or registered dietitian to create a personalized diet plan for weight loss.",
